!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

saving /ˈseɪvɪŋ/

(savings) 

1. N-COUNT A saving is a reduction in the amount of time or money that is used or needed. 节省 

例： You can enjoy a year's membership for just $28 – a saving of $7 off the regular rate. 你只需花$28就可以享受一年的会员资格–比正常会费节省了$7。 

2. N-PLURAL Your savings are the money that you have saved, especially in a bank or a building society. 积蓄; 存款 

例： Her savings were in the First National Bank. 她的存款以前在第一国民银行。

</div>

